{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"It's a great pleasure to be here."},{"time":2000,"text":"It's a great pleasure to speak after"},{"time":4000,"text":"Brian Cox from CERN."},{"time":6000,"text":"I think CERN is the home"},{"time":8000,"text":"of the Large Hadron Collider."},{"time":11000,"text":"What ever happened to the Small Hadron Collider?"},{"time":14000,"text":"Where is the Small Hadron Collider?"},{"time":17000,"text":"Because the Small Hadron Collider once was the big thing."},{"time":20000,"text":"Now, the Small Hadron Collider"},{"time":23000,"text":"is in a cupboard, overlooked and neglected."},{"time":26000,"text":"You know when the Large Hadron Collider started,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and it didn't work, and people tried to work out why,"},{"time":32000,"text":"it was the Small Hadron Collider team"},{"time":35000,"text":"who sabotaged it"},{"time":37000,"text":"because they were so jealous."},{"time":39000,"text":"The whole Hadron Collider family"},{"time":41000,"text":"needs unlocking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"The lesson of Brian's presentation, in a way --"},{"time":46000,"text":"all those fantastic pictures --"},{"time":48000,"text":"is this really:"},{"time":50000,"text":"that vantage point determines everything that you see."},{"time":53000,"text":"What Brian was saying was"},{"time":55000,"text":"science has opened up successively different vantage points"},{"time":57000,"text":"from which we can see ourselves,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and that's why it's so valuable."},{"time":61000,"text":"So the vantage point you take"},{"time":63000,"text":"determines virtually everything that you will see."},{"time":65000,"text":"The question that you will ask"},{"time":67000,"text":"will determine much of the answer that you get."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"And so if you ask this question:"},{"time":72000,"text":"Where would you look to see the future of education?"},{"time":75000,"text":"The answer that we've traditionally given to that"},{"time":78000,"text":"is very straightforward, at least in the last 20 years:"},{"time":80000,"text":"You go to Finland."},{"time":82000,"text":"Finland is the best place in the world to see school systems."},{"time":85000,"text":"The Finns may be a bit boring and depressive and there's a very high suicide rate,"},{"time":88000,"text":"but by golly, they are qualified."},{"time":91000,"text":"And they have absolutely amazing education systems."},{"time":94000,"text":"So we all troop off to Finland,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and we wonder at the social democratic miracle of Finland"},{"time":99000,"text":"and its cultural homogeneity and all the rest of it,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and then we struggle to imagine how we might"},{"time":104000,"text":"bring lessons back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"Well, so, for this last year,"},{"time":108000,"text":"with the help of Cisco who sponsored me,"},{"time":110000,"text":"for some balmy reason, to do this,"},{"time":113000,"text":"I've been looking somewhere else."},{"time":115000,"text":"Because actually radical innovation does sometimes"},{"time":118000,"text":"come from the very best,"},{"time":120000,"text":"but it often comes from places"},{"time":122000,"text":"where you have huge need --"},{"time":124000,"text":"unmet, latent demand --"},{"time":126000,"text":"and not enough resources for traditional solutions to work --"},{"time":129000,"text":"traditional, high-cost solutions,"},{"time":131000,"text":"which depend on professionals,"},{"time":133000,"text":"which is what schools and hospitals are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"So I ended up in places like this."},{"time":137000,"text":"This is a place called Monkey Hill."},{"time":140000,"text":"It's one of the hundreds of favelas in Rio."},{"time":143000,"text":"Most of the population growth of the next 50 years"},{"time":146000,"text":"will be in cities."},{"time":148000,"text":"We'll grow by six cities of 12 million people a year"},{"time":151000,"text":"for the next 30 years."},{"time":153000,"text":"Almost all of that growth will be in the developed world."},{"time":156000,"text":"Almost all of that growth will be"},{"time":158000,"text":"in places like Monkey Hill."},{"time":160000,"text":"This is where you'll find the fastest growing"},{"time":162000,"text":"young populations of the world."},{"time":164000,"text":"So if you want recipes to work --"},{"time":166000,"text":"for virtually anything -- health, education,"},{"time":168000,"text":"government politics"},{"time":170000,"text":"and education --"},{"time":172000,"text":"you have to go to these places."},{"time":174000,"text":"And if you go to these places, you meet people like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"This is a guy called Juanderson."},{"time":178000,"text":"At the age of 14,"},{"time":180000,"text":"in common with many 14-year-olds in the Brazilian education system,"},{"time":183000,"text":"he dropped out of school."},{"time":185000,"text":"It was boring."},{"time":187000,"text":"And Juanderson, instead, went into"},{"time":189000,"text":"what provided kind of opportunity and hope"},{"time":191000,"text":"in the place that he lived, which was the drugs trade."},{"time":194000,"text":"And by the age of 16, with rapid promotion,"},{"time":197000,"text":"he was running the drugs trade in 10 favelas."},{"time":199000,"text":"He was turning over 200,000 dollars a week."},{"time":202000,"text":"He employed 200 people."},{"time":204000,"text":"He was going to be dead by the age of 25."},{"time":206000,"text":"And luckily, he met this guy,"},{"time":208000,"text":"who is Rodrigo Baggio,"},{"time":210000,"text":"the owner of the first laptop to ever appear in Brazil."},{"time":213000,"text":"1994, Rodrigo started something"},{"time":215000,"text":"called CDI,"},{"time":217000,"text":"which took computers"},{"time":219000,"text":"donated by corporations,"},{"time":221000,"text":"put them into community centers in favelas"},{"time":223000,"text":"and created places like this."},{"time":226000,"text":"What turned Juanderson around"},{"time":228000,"text":"was technology for learning"},{"time":230000,"text":"that made learning fun and accessible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"Or you can go to places like this."},{"time":234000,"text":"This is Kibera, which is the largest slum in East Africa."},{"time":237000,"text":"Millions of people living here,"},{"time":239000,"text":"stretched over many kilometers."},{"time":241000,"text":"And there I met these two,"},{"time":243000,"text":"Azra on the left, Maureen on the right."},{"time":245000,"text":"They just finished their Kenyan certificate"},{"time":247000,"text":"of secondary education."},{"time":249000,"text":"That name should tell you that the Kenyan education system"},{"time":252000,"text":"borrows almost everything"},{"time":254000,"text":"from Britain, circa 1950,"},{"time":257000,"text":"but has managed to make it even worse."},{"time":260000,"text":"So there are schools in slums like this."},{"time":262000,"text":"They're places like this."},{"time":264000,"text":"That's where Maureen went to school."},{"time":266000,"text":"They're private schools. There are no state schools in slums."},{"time":269000,"text":"And the education they got was pitiful."},{"time":272000,"text":"It was in places like this. This a school set up by some nuns"},{"time":275000,"text":"in another slum called Nakuru."},{"time":278000,"text":"Half the children in this classroom have no parents"},{"time":281000,"text":"because they've died through AIDS."},{"time":283000,"text":"The other half have one parent"},{"time":285000,"text":"because the other parent has died through AIDS."},{"time":288000,"text":"So the challenges of education"},{"time":290000,"text":"in this kind of place"},{"time":292000,"text":"are not to learn the kings and queens of Kenya or Britain."},{"time":295000,"text":"They are to stay alive, to earn a living,"},{"time":298000,"text":"to not become HIV positive."},{"time":301000,"text":"The one technology that spans rich and poor"},{"time":304000,"text":"in places like this"},{"time":306000,"text":"is not anything to do with industrial technology."},{"time":308000,"text":"It's not to do with electricity or water."},{"time":310000,"text":"It's the mobile phone."},{"time":312000,"text":"If you want to design from scratch"},{"time":314000,"text":"virtually any service in Africa,"},{"time":316000,"text":"you would start now with the mobile phone."},{"time":319000,"text":"Or you could go to places like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"This is a place called the Madangiri Settlement Colony,"},{"time":324000,"text":"which is a very developed slum"},{"time":326000,"text":"about 25 minutes outside New Delhi,"},{"time":329000,"text":"where I met these characters"},{"time":331000,"text":"who showed me around for the day."},{"time":333000,"text":"The remarkable thing about these girls,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and the sign of the kind of social revolution"},{"time":338000,"text":"sweeping through the developing world"},{"time":340000,"text":"is that these girls are not married."},{"time":343000,"text":"Ten years ago, they certainly would have been married."},{"time":345000,"text":"Now they're not married, and they want to go on"},{"time":347000,"text":"to study further, to have a career."},{"time":349000,"text":"They've been brought up by mothers who are illiterate,"},{"time":352000,"text":"who have never ever done homework."},{"time":355000,"text":"All across the developing world there are millions of parents --"},{"time":357000,"text":"tens, hundreds of millions --"},{"time":359000,"text":"who for the first time"},{"time":361000,"text":"are with children doing homework and exams."},{"time":364000,"text":"And the reason they carry on studying"},{"time":366000,"text":"is not because they went to a school like this."},{"time":368000,"text":"This is a private school."},{"time":370000,"text":"This is a fee-pay school. This is a good school."},{"time":372000,"text":"This is the best you can get"},{"time":374000,"text":"in Hyderabad in Indian education."},{"time":377000,"text":"The reason they went on studying was this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"This is a computer installed in the entrance to their slum"},{"time":383000,"text":"by a revolutionary social entrepreneur"},{"time":385000,"text":"called Sugata Mitra"},{"time":387000,"text":"who has conducted the most radical experiments,"},{"time":389000,"text":"showing that children, in the right conditions,"},{"time":392000,"text":"can learn on their own with the help of computers."},{"time":395000,"text":"Those girls have never touched Google."},{"time":398000,"text":"They know nothing about Wikipedia."},{"time":400000,"text":"Imagine what their lives would be like"},{"time":403000,"text":"if you could get that to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"So if you look, as I did,"},{"time":407000,"text":"through this tour,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and by looking at about a hundred case studies"},{"time":412000,"text":"of different social entrepreneurs"},{"time":414000,"text":"working in these very extreme conditions,"},{"time":417000,"text":"look at the recipes that they come up with for learning,"},{"time":420000,"text":"they look nothing like school."},{"time":422000,"text":"What do they look like?"},{"time":424000,"text":"Well, education is a global religion."},{"time":426000,"text":"And education, plus technology,"},{"time":428000,"text":"is a great source of hope."},{"time":430000,"text":"You can go to places like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"This is a school three hours outside of Sao Paulo."},{"time":436000,"text":"Most of the children there have parents who are illiterate."},{"time":439000,"text":"Many of them don't have electricity at home."},{"time":442000,"text":"But they find it completely obvious"},{"time":445000,"text":"to use computers, websites,"},{"time":447000,"text":"make videos, so on and so forth."},{"time":449000,"text":"When you go to places like this"},{"time":451000,"text":"what you see is that"},{"time":453000,"text":"education in these settings"},{"time":456000,"text":"works by pull, not push."},{"time":458000,"text":"Most of our education system is push."},{"time":460000,"text":"I was literally pushed to school."},{"time":462000,"text":"When you get to school, things are pushed at you:"},{"time":464000,"text":"knowledge, exams,"},{"time":466000,"text":"systems, timetables."},{"time":468000,"text":"If you want to attract people like Juanderson"},{"time":470000,"text":"who could, for instance,"},{"time":472000,"text":"buy guns, wear jewelry,"},{"time":474000,"text":"ride motorbikes and get girls"},{"time":476000,"text":"through the drugs trade,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and you want to attract him into education,"},{"time":480000,"text":"having a compulsory curriculum doesn't really make sense."},{"time":483000,"text":"That isn't really going to attract him."},{"time":485000,"text":"You need to pull him."},{"time":487000,"text":"And so education needs to work by pull, not push."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"And so the idea of a curriculum"},{"time":492000,"text":"is completely irrelevant in a setting like this."},{"time":494000,"text":"You need to start education"},{"time":496000,"text":"from things that make a difference"},{"time":498000,"text":"to them in their settings."},{"time":500000,"text":"What does that?"},{"time":502000,"text":"Well, the key is motivation, and there are two aspects to it."},{"time":505000,"text":"One is to deliver extrinsic motivation,"},{"time":508000,"text":"that education has a payoff."},{"time":510000,"text":"Our education systems all work"},{"time":513000,"text":"on the principle that there is a payoff,"},{"time":515000,"text":"but you have to wait quite a long time."},{"time":517000,"text":"That's too long if you're poor."},{"time":519000,"text":"Waiting 10 years for the payoff from education"},{"time":522000,"text":"is too long when you need to meet daily needs,"},{"time":525000,"text":"when you've got siblings to look after"},{"time":527000,"text":"or a business to help with."},{"time":529000,"text":"So you need education to be relevant and help people"},{"time":531000,"text":"to make a living there and then, often."},{"time":534000,"text":"And you also need to make it intrinsically interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537000,"text":"So time and again, I found people like this."},{"time":540000,"text":"This is an amazing guy, Sebastiao Rocha,"},{"time":543000,"text":"in Belo Horizonte,"},{"time":545000,"text":"in the third largest city in Brazil."},{"time":547000,"text":"He's invented more than 200 games"},{"time":549000,"text":"to teach virtually any subject under the sun."},{"time":552000,"text":"In the schools and communities"},{"time":554000,"text":"that Taio works in,"},{"time":556000,"text":"the day always starts in a circle"},{"time":558000,"text":"and always starts from a question."},{"time":561000,"text":"Imagine an education system that started from questions,"},{"time":564000,"text":"not from knowledge to be imparted,"},{"time":566000,"text":"or started from a game, not from a lesson,"},{"time":569000,"text":"or started from the premise"},{"time":571000,"text":"that you have to engage people first"},{"time":574000,"text":"before you can possibly teach them."},{"time":576000,"text":"Our education systems,"},{"time":578000,"text":"you do all that stuff afterward, if you're lucky,"},{"time":580000,"text":"sport, drama, music."},{"time":582000,"text":"These things, they teach through."},{"time":585000,"text":"They attract people to learning"},{"time":587000,"text":"because it's really a dance project"},{"time":589000,"text":"or a circus project"},{"time":591000,"text":"or, the best example of all --"},{"time":593000,"text":"El Sistema in Venezuela --"},{"time":595000,"text":"it's a music project."},{"time":597000,"text":"And so you attract people through that into learning,"},{"time":599000,"text":"not adding that on after"},{"time":601000,"text":"all the learning has been done"},{"time":603000,"text":"and you've eaten your cognitive greens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"So El Sistema in Venezuela"},{"time":608000,"text":"uses a violin as a technology of learning."},{"time":611000,"text":"Taio Rocha uses making soap"},{"time":614000,"text":"as a technology of learning."},{"time":616000,"text":"And what you find when you go to these schemes"},{"time":618000,"text":"is that they use people and places"},{"time":620000,"text":"in incredibly creative ways."},{"time":622000,"text":"Masses of peer learning."},{"time":624000,"text":"How do you get learning to people"},{"time":626000,"text":"when there are no teachers,"},{"time":628000,"text":"when teachers won't come, when you can't afford them,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and even if you do get teachers,"},{"time":633000,"text":"what they teach isn't relevant to the communities that they serve?"},{"time":636000,"text":"Well, you create your own teachers."},{"time":638000,"text":"You create peer-to-peer learning,"},{"time":640000,"text":"or you create para-teachers, or you bring in specialist skills."},{"time":643000,"text":"But you find ways to get learning that's relevant to people"},{"time":646000,"text":"through technology, people and places that are different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"So this is a school in a bus"},{"time":651000,"text":"on a building site"},{"time":654000,"text":"in Pune, the fastest growing city in Asia."},{"time":657000,"text":"Pune has 5,000 building sites."},{"time":660000,"text":"It has 30,000 children"},{"time":662000,"text":"on those building sites."},{"time":664000,"text":"That's one city."},{"time":666000,"text":"Imagine that urban explosion"},{"time":668000,"text":"that's going to take place across the developing world"},{"time":671000,"text":"and how many thousands of children"},{"time":673000,"text":"will spend their school years on building sites."},{"time":675000,"text":"Well, this is a very simple scheme"},{"time":677000,"text":"to get the learning to them through a bus."},{"time":680000,"text":"And they all treat learning,"},{"time":683000,"text":"not as some sort of academic, analytical activity,"},{"time":686000,"text":"but as that's something that's productive,"},{"time":688000,"text":"something you make,"},{"time":690000,"text":"something that you can do, perhaps earn a living from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"So I met this character, Steven."},{"time":696000,"text":"He'd spent three years in Nairobi living on the streets"},{"time":699000,"text":"because his parents had died of AIDS."},{"time":701000,"text":"And he was finally brought back into school,"},{"time":703000,"text":"not by the offer of GCSEs,"},{"time":705000,"text":"but by the offer of learning how to become a carpenter,"},{"time":708000,"text":"a practical making skill."},{"time":710000,"text":"So the trendiest schools in the world,"},{"time":712000,"text":"High Tech High and others,"},{"time":714000,"text":"they espouse a philosophy of learning as productive activity."},{"time":717000,"text":"Here, there isn't really an option."},{"time":719000,"text":"Learning has to be productive"},{"time":721000,"text":"in order for it to make sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724000,"text":"And finally, they have a different model of scale,"},{"time":727000,"text":"and it's a Chinese restaurant model"},{"time":729000,"text":"of how to scale."},{"time":731000,"text":"And I learned it from this guy,"},{"time":733000,"text":"who is an amazing character."},{"time":735000,"text":"He's probably the most remarkable social entrepreneur"},{"time":737000,"text":"in education in the world."},{"time":739000,"text":"His name is Madhav Chavan,"},{"time":741000,"text":"and he created something called Pratham."},{"time":743000,"text":"And Pratham runs preschool play groups"},{"time":746000,"text":"for, now, 21 million children in India."},{"time":749000,"text":"It's the largest NGO in education in the world."},{"time":752000,"text":"And it also supports working-class kids going into Indian schools."},{"time":755000,"text":"He's a complete revolutionary."},{"time":757000,"text":"He's actually a trade union organizer by background,"},{"time":760000,"text":"and that's how he learned the skills"},{"time":762000,"text":"to build his organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"When they got to a certain stage,"},{"time":766000,"text":"Pratham got big enough to attract"},{"time":768000,"text":"some pro bono support from McKinsey."},{"time":770000,"text":"McKinsey came along and looked at his model and said,"},{"time":773000,"text":"\"You know what you should do with this, Madhav?"},{"time":775000,"text":"You should turn it into McDonald's."},{"time":777000,"text":"And what you do when you go to any new site"},{"time":779000,"text":"is you kind of roll out a franchise."},{"time":781000,"text":"And it's the same wherever you go."},{"time":783000,"text":"It's reliable and people know exactly where they are."},{"time":786000,"text":"And there will be no mistakes.\""},{"time":788000,"text":"And Madhav said,"},{"time":790000,"text":"\"Why do we have to do it that way?"},{"time":792000,"text":"Why can't we do it more like the Chinese restaurants?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"There are Chinese restaurants everywhere,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but there is no Chinese restaurant chain."},{"time":800000,"text":"Yet, everyone knows what is a Chinese restaurant."},{"time":802000,"text":"They know what to expect, even though it'll be subtly different"},{"time":805000,"text":"and the colors will be different and the name will be different."},{"time":807000,"text":"You know a Chinese restaurant when you see it."},{"time":810000,"text":"These people work with the Chinese restaurant model --"},{"time":813000,"text":"same principles, different applications and different settings --"},{"time":816000,"text":"not the McDonald's model."},{"time":818000,"text":"The McDonald's model scales."},{"time":820000,"text":"The Chinese restaurant model spreads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"So mass education"},{"time":825000,"text":"started with social entrepreneurship"},{"time":827000,"text":"in the 19th century."},{"time":829000,"text":"And that's desperately what we need again"},{"time":831000,"text":"on a global scale."},{"time":833000,"text":"And what can we learn from all of that?"},{"time":835000,"text":"Well, we can learn a lot"},{"time":837000,"text":"because our education systems"},{"time":839000,"text":"are failing desperately in many ways."},{"time":841000,"text":"They fail to reach the people"},{"time":843000,"text":"they most need to serve."},{"time":845000,"text":"They often hit their target but miss the point."},{"time":848000,"text":"Improvement is increasingly"},{"time":850000,"text":"difficult to organize;"},{"time":852000,"text":"our faith in these systems, incredibly fraught."},{"time":855000,"text":"And this is just a very simple way of"},{"time":857000,"text":"understanding what kind of innovation,"},{"time":860000,"text":"what kind of different design we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863000,"text":"There are two basic types of innovation."},{"time":865000,"text":"There's sustaining innovation,"},{"time":867000,"text":"which will sustain an existing institution or an organization,"},{"time":870000,"text":"and disruptive innovation"},{"time":872000,"text":"that will break it apart, create some different way of doing it."},{"time":875000,"text":"There are formal settings --"},{"time":877000,"text":"schools, colleges, hospitals --"},{"time":879000,"text":"in which innovation can take place,"},{"time":881000,"text":"and informal settings -- communities,"},{"time":883000,"text":"families, social networks."},{"time":885000,"text":"Almost all our effort goes in this box,"},{"time":887000,"text":"sustaining innovation in formal settings,"},{"time":890000,"text":"getting a better version"},{"time":892000,"text":"of the essentially Bismarckian school system"},{"time":894000,"text":"that developed in the 19th century."},{"time":897000,"text":"And as I said, the trouble with this is that,"},{"time":899000,"text":"in the developing world"},{"time":901000,"text":"there just aren't teachers to make this model work."},{"time":903000,"text":"You'd need millions and millions of teachers"},{"time":906000,"text":"in China, India, Nigeria"},{"time":908000,"text":"and the rest of developing world to meet need."},{"time":911000,"text":"And in our system, we know"},{"time":913000,"text":"that simply doing more of this won't eat into"},{"time":916000,"text":"deep educational inequalities,"},{"time":918000,"text":"especially in inner cities"},{"time":920000,"text":"and former industrial areas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"So that's why we need three more kinds of innovation."},{"time":925000,"text":"We need more reinvention."},{"time":927000,"text":"And all around the world now you see"},{"time":929000,"text":"more and more schools reinventing themselves."},{"time":932000,"text":"They're recognizably schools, but they look different."},{"time":935000,"text":"There are Big Picture schools"},{"time":937000,"text":"in the U.S. and Australia."},{"time":939000,"text":"There are Kunskapsskolan schools"},{"time":941000,"text":"in Sweden."},{"time":943000,"text":"Of 14 of them,"},{"time":946000,"text":"only two of them are in schools."},{"time":948000,"text":"Most of them are in other buildings not designed as schools."},{"time":951000,"text":"There is an amazing school in Northen Queensland"},{"time":953000,"text":"called Jaringan."},{"time":955000,"text":"And they all have the same kind of features:"},{"time":957000,"text":"highly collaborative, very personalized,"},{"time":960000,"text":"often pervasive technology,"},{"time":963000,"text":"learning that starts from questions"},{"time":965000,"text":"and problems and projects,"},{"time":967000,"text":"not from knowledge and curriculum."},{"time":969000,"text":"So we certainly need more of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971000,"text":"But because so many of the issues in education"},{"time":974000,"text":"aren't just in school,"},{"time":976000,"text":"they're in family and community,"},{"time":978000,"text":"what you also need, definitely,"},{"time":980000,"text":"is more on the right hand side."},{"time":982000,"text":"You need efforts to supplement schools."},{"time":985000,"text":"The most famous of these is Reggio Emilia in Italy,"},{"time":988000,"text":"the family-based learning system"},{"time":991000,"text":"to support and encourage people in schools."},{"time":994000,"text":"The most exciting is the Harlem Children's Zone,"},{"time":997000,"text":"which over 10 years, led by Geoffrey Canada,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"has, through a mixture of schooling"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and family and community projects,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"attempted to transform not just education in schools,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"but the entire culture and aspiration"},{"time":1010000,"text":"of about 10,000 families in Harlem."},{"time":1013000,"text":"We need more of that"},{"time":1015000,"text":"completely new and radical thinking."},{"time":1017000,"text":"You can go to places an hour away, less,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"from this room,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"just down the road, which need that,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"which need radicalism of a kind that we haven't imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028000,"text":"And finally, you need transformational innovation"},{"time":1030000,"text":"that could imagine getting learning to people"},{"time":1032000,"text":"in completely new and different ways."},{"time":1035000,"text":"So we are on the verge, 2015,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"of an amazing achievement,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"the schoolification of the world."},{"time":1043000,"text":"Every child up to the age of 15 who wants a place in school"},{"time":1046000,"text":"will be able to have one in 2015."},{"time":1048000,"text":"It's an amazing thing."},{"time":1050000,"text":"But it is,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"unlike cars, which have developed"},{"time":1054000,"text":"so rapidly and orderly,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"actually the school system is recognizably"},{"time":1059000,"text":"an inheritance from the 19th century,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"from a Bismarkian model of German schooling"},{"time":1064000,"text":"that got taken up by English reformers,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"and often by"},{"time":1070000,"text":"religious missionaries,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"taken up in the United States"},{"time":1074000,"text":"as a force of social cohesion,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"and then in Japan and South Korea as they developed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"It's recognizably 19th century in its roots."},{"time":1081000,"text":"And of course it's a huge achievement."},{"time":1083000,"text":"And of course it will bring great things."},{"time":1085000,"text":"It will bring skills and learning and reading."},{"time":1088000,"text":"But it will also lay waste to imagination."},{"time":1091000,"text":"It will lay waste to appetite. It will lay waste to social confidence."},{"time":1094000,"text":"It will stratify society"},{"time":1096000,"text":"as much as it liberates it."},{"time":1098000,"text":"And we are bequeathing to the developing world"},{"time":1100000,"text":"school systems that they will now spend"},{"time":1103000,"text":"a century trying to reform."},{"time":1105000,"text":"That is why we need really radical thinking,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"and why radical thinking is now"},{"time":1110000,"text":"more possible and more needed than ever in how we learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}